## 3.1.6 (2026-03-24)

### New providers:

-   **Gladia STT** — real-time speech-to-text via Gladia API with WebSocket live streaming, speaker diarization, and code-switching support
-   **Deepgram STT** — real-time speech-to-text via Deepgram API with Nova-3 model, built-in translation to any target language via Google Cloud, and speaker diarization

### Monitor improvements:

-   log entries can now be sorted newest-first or oldest-first via the toolbar
-   placeholder screen redesigned: the play button is now clickable to start a session directly
-   active transcription provider is highlighted in the placeholder; configured providers can be switched without going to Settings
-   TTS active provider is also shown and switchable from the placeholder screen

### Account & cloud:

-   user authentication and account management added (sign in / sign out via Config sidebar)
-   trial usage display with live countdown when using Transkit Cloud transcription
-   pre-debit usage model implemented for cloud sessions

## 3.1.1 (2026-03-20)

### Changes:

-   removed "Local" language detection engine (powered by `lingua`) to reduce installer size by ~15–20 MB
-   users previously on "Local" detect will automatically fall back to Google detection
-   the "Local" option has been removed from Settings → Translate → Detect Engine

## 3.1.0 (2026-03-18)

### New feature:

-   first TransKit release line based on independent roadmap
-   realtime monitor enhancements for meetings and live translation
-   sub mode, AI suggestion, bookmarks, and transcript auto-save
-   TTS providers with BYO API model (free + premium options)
-   refreshed multilingual READMEs (EN/VI/CN/KR) with streamlined install/contribution guides

### Build & release:

-   clarified CI release flow and platform packaging matrix
-   aligned release documentation for updater artifacts and platform installers
